            "date": "2012-03-03 00:45:15", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Precise does provide 32 bit glu dev libraries on amd64, you're compiling a 32 bit app and you need 32 bit dependencies that can't be installed at the same time as the amd64 ones in this case. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "If it's not showing up in the repositories that's no fault of mesa's, your dpkg configuration must be messed up and has i386 disabled. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Do you have /etc/dpkg/dpkg.cfg.d/multiarch with foreign-architecture i386 in it?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "sarvatt", 
            "email": "sarvatt"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-03 02:13:41", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Yes, I have multiarch enabled. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I can build wine in Oneiric amd64 without problems. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "So do you mean that libglu-mesa-dev:amd64 supplies the 32 bit dev libraries as well?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "rockorequin", 
            "email": "rockorequin"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-03 02:55:40", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The wine wiki has this tidbit:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\"On 12.04, which now has multiarch support, things are trickier: sudo apt-get build-dep wine1.4:i386. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Doing this may very well remove your ability to build 64-bit programs.\"\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This doesn't work (the sources for wine1.4:i386 aren't found even if I add the PPA they suggest), but the hint for me at least is that you need libglu1-mesa-dev:i386, meaning you can't have libglu1-mesa-dev installed.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "So I manually removed libglu1-mesa-dev and then installed libglu1-mesa-dev:i386 and now I can build wine. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Of course libglu1-mesa-dev:i386 doesn't appear in the repos so I have to download the deb file manually.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "ie there is a workaround, but it's a huge pain having to do this.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Why does libglu1-mesa-dev:i386 conflict with libglu1-mesa-dev:amd64? ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Isn't the whole idea behind going multiarch to let you install both the 32 bit and 64 bit packages side by side to make things easier?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "rockorequin", 
            "email": "rockorequin"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-04 02:04:40", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Some more research shows that the libglu1-mesa-dev package doesn't include the file /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/libGLU.so. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Since it conflicts with the i386 package, shouldn't it include this file also if it is to include the required 32 bit dev files?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "As a workaround, if I have the libglu1-mesa:i386 package installed I can symlink the file /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/libGLU.so.1 to the missing file, and then I can build wine with just the libglu1-mesa-dev:amd64 package installed.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The problem is widespread, eg libxrandr-dev, libxi-dev, libsane-dev, etc all exhibit this problem.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "What is the recommended solution? ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I don't follow what is meant in comment 4 about stitching the components together afterwards. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Should the libglu1-mesa:i386 package include libGLU.so as a symlink?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
